title: North Korea Launches Unidentified Projectile Off Its East Coast, South Korea Says
sub_head: Weapons test is Pyongyang’s second of 2022, following Jan. 5 ballistic missile launch
body:
SEOUL—North Korea launched an unidentified projectile off its east coast on Tuesday, South Korea’s military said, marking the Kim Jong Un regime’s second weapons test in under a week.
The weapon type, exact time of the launch and flight distance couldn’t immediately be learned.
